HEADWORD: Ratter
<hw>Rat"ter</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧t"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, rats, as one who deserts his
party.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anything which catches rats; esp., a dog trained to
catch rats; a rat terrier. See <er>Terrier</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rattinet</ent>⟦br⟧
